European Coal Advances for a Fourth Day, Trades at $127 a Ton

-- B y   Y i n g   D i a o
-- 
2011-08-15T12:13:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/european-coal-advances-for-a-fourth-day-trades-at-127-a-ton.html
European coal rose for a fourth day.  Thermal coal burned to generate electricity climbed 40
cents, or 0.3 percent, to $127 a metric ton by 12:34 p.m. in
 London . Price slipped 0.2 percent last week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ying Diao in London at 
 dying6@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 